      "comment_id" : 98714173,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "in AS 3.4 enabling the &quot;org.gradle.jvmargs=-Xmx2048m -XX:MaxPermSize=512m -XX:+HeapDumpOnOutOfMemoryError -Dfile.encoding=UTF-8&quot; in the gradle.properties file solved the issue for me"
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 166826,
      "reputation" : 73,
      "user_id" : 2007502,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/4sAsu.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Selvaganesan Saminathan",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2007502/selvaganesan-saminathan"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "community_owned_date" : 1460987236,
    "score" : 46,
    "last_activity_date" : 1484995683,
    "last_edit_date" : 1484995683,
    "creation_date" : 1460987236,
    "answer_id" : 36695880,
    "question_id" : 25013638,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>This new issue is caused by the latest version of Android.</p>\n\n<p>Go to your project root folder, open <code>gradle.properties</code>, and add the following options:</p>\n\n<pre><code>org.gradle.daemon=true\n\norg.gradle.jvmargs=-Xmx2048m -XX:MaxPermSize=512m -XX:+HeapDumpOnOutOfMemoryError -Dfile.encoding=UTF-8\n\norg.gradle.parallel=true\n\norg.gradle.configureondemand=true\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Then add these changes in your <code>build.gradle</code> file:</p>\n\n<pre><code>dexOptions {\n        incremental = true\n        preDexLibraries = false\n        javaMaxHeapSize \"4g\" // 2g should be also OK\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
